      </div>
      <ul class="faq-list">

        <li>
          <a data-toggle="collapse" class="" href="#faq1">Who are Edukita’s teachers? <i class="fa fa-angle-up"></i></a>
          <div id="faq1" class="collapse show" data-parent=".faq-list">
            <p>Our teachers are native English-speaking teachers. They bring their own expertise and strengths to our
              program. We will match you to a teacher based on your needs and goals.</p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li data-aos-delay="200">
          <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq2" class="collapsed">How much English do I need to know before joining
            Edukita? <i class="fa fa-angle-up"></i></a>
          <div id="faq2" class="collapse" data-parent=".faq-list">
            <p>We are open to all students of all proficiency levels (from beginners to advanced). We will customize
              your curriculum based on your needs and goals. All we need is a healthy dose of curiosity and hunger for
              learning.</p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li data-aos-delay="300">
          <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq3" class="collapsed">What age groups do you accept? <i
              class="fa fa-angle-up"></i></a>
          <div id="faq3" class="collapse" data-parent=".faq-list">
            <p>
              We accept students of age 6-18 (SD/Primary School to SMA/High School).
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li data-aos-delay="400">
          <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq4" class="collapsed">How much does it cost? <i
              class="fa fa-angle-up"></i></a>
          <div id="faq4" class="collapse" data-parent=".faq-list">
            <p>
              Our service costs much less than what you would normally pay. Please reach out to us so our advisors can
              help you choose the right learning format that suits your needs.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li data-aos-delay="500">
          <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq5" class="collapsed">How long is a lesson? <i
              class="fa fa-angle-up"></i></a>
          <div id="faq5" class="collapse" data-parent=".faq-list">
            <p>
              Each lesson is an interactive 40 minute session with a native English-speaking teacher. A lesson consists
              of an overview of key concepts, in-class exercises and live practice with the teacher.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li data-aos-delay="600">
          <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq6" class="collapsed">How long does it take to complete a course? <i
              class="fa fa-angle-up"></i></a>
          <div id="faq6" class="collapse" data-parent=".faq-list">
            <p>
              While a course typically takes between 4-6 months, we don’t set a definite timeline to our students. We
              believe that each student learns at her own pace. We don’t want to rush through materials for the sake of
              completion.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li data-aos-delay="500">
          <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq6" class="collapsed">In a group lesson format, how big are the classrooms?
            <i class="fa fa-angle-up"></i></a>
          <div id="faq6" class="collapse" data-parent=".faq-list">
            <p>
              We keep our group size to fewer than 10 students to ensure a high level of engagement.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li data-aos-delay="500">
          <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq7" class="collapsed">What technology or tools do I need to have? <i
              class="fa fa-angle-up"></i></a>
          <div id="faq7" class="collapse" data-parent=".faq-list">
            <p>
              All you need is access to a computer, a tablet, or a smartphone, and a stable internet connection.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li data-aos-delay="500">
          <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq8" class="collapsed">Do your coaches help with your school homework? <i
              class="fa fa-angle-up"></i></a>
          <div id="faq8" class="collapse" data-parent=".faq-list">
            <p>
              When you join Edukita, we will develop a curriculum for you. We are more than happy to devote a limited
              portion of class time to answer questions on school assignments. However, most class time will be spent on
              your own learning plan.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li data-aos-delay="500">
